{
  "texts": [
    "And secondly, microlensing is the only probe for peculiar velocities of galaxies at high redshifts (z > 0.1, Mediavilla et al. 2016).",
    "Such velocities can in turn be used to constrain the growth of structure (e.g.",
    "Koda et al. 2014) and shed more light into the σ 8 tension between early and late Universe (Di Valentino et al. 2021).",
    "The two main and invaluable sources for microlensing data in the next decade will be the allsky surveys by the Vera Rubin observatory and the Euclid satellite, both starting to provide data within 2023.",
    "The former, will provide ∼ 800 epochs across 6 bands over a decade for each patch of sky (on average), while the latter will carry out a survey at a much higher spatial resolution (space-based)."
  ]
}